Head. Eyes bare. Temporals consisting of 10–11 setae including 6–7 inner and 4 outer verticals. Palp 5-segmented, not reduced; length (in μm) of segments: 35, 45, 63, 136, 225; palpomere 3 (
Fig. 35
) with 3 sensilla clavata, palpomere 4 (
Fig. 36
) with 2 circular area of microtrichia placed proximally and distally. Clypeus with 6 setae in 2 rows.

